{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":360,"text":"What does a working mother look like?"},{"time":3240,"text":"If you ask the Internet,\nthis is what you'll be told."},{"time":6520,"text":"Never mind that this is\nwhat you'll actually produce"},{"time":10970,"text":"if you attempt to work at a computer\nwith a baby on your lap."}]},{"cues":[{"time":13880,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":15440,"text":"But no, this isn't a working mother."},{"time":18360,"text":"You'll notice a theme in these photos.\nWe'll look at a lot of them."},{"time":21560,"text":"That theme is amazing natural lighting,"},{"time":24000,"text":"which, as we all know,"},{"time":27160,"text":"is the hallmark\nof every American workplace."}]},{"cues":[{"time":31360,"text":"There are thousands of images like these."},{"time":34840,"text":"Just put the term \"working mother\"\ninto any Google image search engine,"},{"time":38280,"text":"stock photo site."},{"time":39560,"text":"They're all over the Internet,"},{"time":41040,"text":"they're topping\nblog posts and news pieces,"},{"time":43440,"text":"and I've become kind of obsessed with them\nand the lie that they tell us"},{"time":47800,"text":"and the comfort that they give us,"},{"time":49800,"text":"that when it comes\nto new working motherhood in America,"},{"time":53240,"text":"everything's fine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":55040,"text":"But it's not fine."},{"time":56640,"text":"As a country, we are sending\nmillions of women back to work"},{"time":60080,"text":"every year, incredibly\nand kind of horrifically soon"},{"time":64040,"text":"after they give birth."},{"time":65720,"text":"That's a moral problem"},{"time":67440,"text":"but today I'm also going to tell you\nwhy it's an economic problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":71360,"text":"I got so annoyed and obsessed\nwith the unreality of these images,"},{"time":75000,"text":"which look nothing like my life,"},{"time":77040,"text":"that I recently decided to shoot and star\nin a parody series of stock photos"},{"time":82240,"text":"that I hoped the world would start to use"},{"time":84400,"text":"just showing the really awkward reality\nof going back to work"},{"time":88680,"text":"when your baby's food source\nis attached to your body."},{"time":93320,"text":"I'm just going to show you two of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":95720,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":97800,"text":"Nothing says \"Give that girl a promotion\"\nlike leaking breast milk"},{"time":100920,"text":"through your dress during a presentation."},{"time":103080,"text":"You'll notice that there's\nno baby in this photo,"},{"time":105520,"text":"because that's not how this works,"},{"time":108160,"text":"not for most working mothers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":110520,"text":"Did you know, and this will ruin your day,"},{"time":112600,"text":"that every time a toilet is flushed,\nits contents are aerosolized"},{"time":115800,"text":"and they'll stay airborne for hours?"},{"time":118240,"text":"And yet, for many new working mothers,"},{"time":121000,"text":"this is the only place during the day\nthat they can find to make food"},{"time":124280,"text":"for their newborn babies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":126880,"text":"I put these things,\na whole dozen of them, into the world."},{"time":130360,"text":"I wanted to make a point."},{"time":132000,"text":"I didn't know what I was also doing\nwas opening a door,"},{"time":135440,"text":"because now, total strangers\nfrom all walks of life"},{"time":139000,"text":"write to me all the time"},{"time":140960,"text":"just to tell me what it's like\nfor them to go back to work"},{"time":144840,"text":"within days or weeks of having a baby."},{"time":147880,"text":"I'm going to share\n10 of their stories with you today."},{"time":150480,"text":"They are totally real,\nsome of them are very raw,"},{"time":153880,"text":"and not one of them\nlooks anything like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":158360,"text":"Here's the first."},{"time":160160,"text":"\"I was an active duty\nservice member at a federal prison."},{"time":163880,"text":"I returned to work after the maximum\nallowed eight weeks for my C-section."},{"time":168280,"text":"A male coworker was annoyed\nthat I had been out on 'vacation,'"},{"time":172360,"text":"so he intentionally opened the door on me\nwhile I was pumping breast milk"},{"time":175813,"text":"and stood in the doorway\nwith inmates in the hallway.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":179880,"text":"Most of the stories that these women,\ntotal strangers, send to me now,"},{"time":183200,"text":"are not actually even about breastfeeding."}]},{"cues":[{"time":185480,"text":"A woman wrote to me to say,"},{"time":187400,"text":"\"I gave birth to twins and went back\nto work after seven unpaid weeks."},{"time":192200,"text":"Emotionally, I was a wreck."},{"time":193880,"text":"Physically, I had a severe hemorrhage\nduring labor, and major tearing,"},{"time":198240,"text":"so I could barely get up, sit or walk."},{"time":201000,"text":"My employer told me I wasn't allowed\nto use my available vacation days"},{"time":204880,"text":"because it was budget season.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":207800,"text":"I've come to believe that we can't look\nsituations like these in the eye"},{"time":212440,"text":"because then we'd be horrified,"},{"time":214280,"text":"and if we get horrified\nthen we have to do something about it."},{"time":217360,"text":"So we choose to look at,\nand believe, this image."},{"time":221240,"text":"I don't really know\nwhat's going on in this picture,"},{"time":223720,"text":"because I find it weird\nand slightly creepy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":226400,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":227840,"text":"Like, what is she doing?"},{"time":229080,"text":"But I know what it tells us."},{"time":233120,"text":"It tells us that everything's fine."},{"time":235680,"text":"This working mother, all working mothers\nand all of their babies, are fine."},{"time":239440,"text":"There's nothing to see here."},{"time":241440,"text":"And anyway, women have made a choice,"},{"time":244880,"text":"so none of it's even our problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":247200,"text":"I want to break this choice thing\ndown into two parts."},{"time":250160,"text":"The first choice says\nthat women have chosen to work."},{"time":253800,"text":"So, that's not true."},{"time":256040,"text":"Today in America, women make up\n47 percent of the workforce,"},{"time":261279,"text":"and in 40 percent of American households"},{"time":263280,"text":"a woman is the sole\nor primary breadwinner."},{"time":266840,"text":"Our paid work is a part, a huge part,\nof the engine of this economy,"},{"time":271400,"text":"and it is essential\nfor the engines of our families."},{"time":274200,"text":"On a national level,\nour paid work is not optional."}]},{"cues":[{"time":278400,"text":"Choice number two says that women\nare choosing to have babies,"},{"time":281360,"text":"so women alone should bear\nthe consequences of those choices."},{"time":286200,"text":"You know, that's one of those things"},{"time":288000,"text":"that when you hear it in passing,\ncan sound correct."},{"time":290480,"text":"I didn't make you have a baby."},{"time":291933,"text":"I certainly wasn't there\nwhen that happened."},{"time":294040,"text":"But that stance\nignores a fundamental truth,"},{"time":300080,"text":"which is that our procreation\non a national scale is not optional."},{"time":305000,"text":"The babies that women, many of them\nworking women, are having today,"},{"time":309520,"text":"will one day fill our workforce,\nprotect our shores,"},{"time":312760,"text":"make up our tax base."},{"time":314600,"text":"Our procreation\non a national scale is not optional."},{"time":318800,"text":"These aren't choices."},{"time":320200,"text":"We need women to work.\nWe need working women to have babies."},{"time":324040,"text":"So we should make\ndoing those things at the same time"},{"time":326541,"text":"at least palatable, right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":328960,"text":"OK, this is pop quiz time:"},{"time":331680,"text":"what percentage of working\nwomen in America do you think"},{"time":334640,"text":"have no access to paid maternity leave?"},{"time":339440,"text":"88 percent."},{"time":341873,"text":"88 percent of working mothers\nwill not get one minute of paid leave"},{"time":345040,"text":"after they have a baby."}]},{"cues":[{"time":346680,"text":"So now you're thinking about unpaid leave."},{"time":350320,"text":"It exists in America.\nIt's called FMLA. It does not work."},{"time":353920,"text":"Because of the way it's structured,\nall kinds of exceptions,"},{"time":356920,"text":"half of new mothers are ineligible for it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":360960,"text":"Here's what that looks like."},{"time":364320,"text":"\"We adopted our son."},{"time":366160,"text":"When I got the call, the day he was born,\nI had to take off work."},{"time":370400,"text":"I had not been there long enough\nto qualify for FMLA,"},{"time":373560,"text":"so I wasn't eligible for unpaid leave."},{"time":376320,"text":"When I took time off\nto meet my newborn son,"},{"time":378760,"text":"I lost my job.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":381840,"text":"These corporate stock photos\nhide another reality, another layer."},{"time":386760,"text":"Of those who do have access\nto just that unpaid leave,"},{"time":390400,"text":"most women can't afford\nto take much of it at all."},{"time":393600,"text":"A nurse told me, \"I didn't qualify\nfor short-term disability"},{"time":397120,"text":"because my pregnancy\nwas considered a preexisting condition."},{"time":401200,"text":"We used up all of our tax returns\nand half of our savings"},{"time":403891,"text":"during my six unpaid weeks."},{"time":405760,"text":"We just couldn't manage any longer."},{"time":407520,"text":"Physically it was hard,\nbut emotionally it was worse."},{"time":410080,"text":"I struggled for months\nbeing away from my son.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":413080,"text":"So this decision\nto go back to work so early,"},{"time":416000,"text":"it's a rational economic decision\ndriven by family finances,"},{"time":420200,"text":"but it's often physically horrific"},{"time":422480,"text":"because putting a human\ninto the world is messy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":426040,"text":"A waitress told me,"},{"time":427480,"text":"\"With my first baby, I was back\nat work five weeks postpartum."},{"time":431040,"text":"With my second, I had to have\nmajor surgery after giving birth,"},{"time":434120,"text":"so I waited until six weeks to go back."},{"time":437160,"text":"I had third degree tears.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":440880,"text":"23 percent of new\nworking mothers in America"},{"time":443960,"text":"will be back on the job\nwithin two weeks of giving birth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":450320,"text":"\"I worked as a bartender and cook,\naverage of 75 hours a week while pregnant."},{"time":455000,"text":"I had to return to work\nbefore my baby was a month old,"},{"time":457640,"text":"working 60 hours a week."},{"time":459680,"text":"One of my coworkers was only able\nto afford 10 days off with her baby.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":464760,"text":"Of course, this isn't just a scenario\nwith economic and physical implications."},{"time":468960,"text":"Childbirth is, and always will be,\nan enormous psychological event."}]},{"cues":[{"time":474160,"text":"A teacher told me,"},{"time":476280,"text":"\"I returned to work\neight weeks after my son was born."},{"time":479280,"text":"I already suffer from anxiety,"},{"time":481200,"text":"but the panic attacks I had prior\nto returning to work were unbearable.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":486320,"text":"Statistically speaking,"},{"time":488440,"text":"the shorter a woman's leave\nafter having a baby,"},{"time":491160,"text":"the more likely she will be to suffer\nfrom postpartum mood disorders"},{"time":494400,"text":"like depression and anxiety,"},{"time":496520,"text":"and among many potential\nconsequences of those disorders,"},{"time":500560,"text":"suicide is the second\nmost common cause of death"},{"time":503720,"text":"in a woman's first year postpartum."}]},{"cues":[{"time":507240,"text":"Heads up that this next story --"},{"time":508840,"text":"I've never met this woman,\nbut I find it hard to get through."}]},{"cues":[{"time":513440,"text":"\"I feel tremendous grief and rage\nthat I lost an essential,"},{"time":517640,"text":"irreplaceable and formative\ntime with my son."},{"time":521520,"text":"Labor and delivery\nleft me feeling absolutely broken."},{"time":524960,"text":"For months, all I remember\nis the screaming: colic, they said."},{"time":529640,"text":"On the inside, I was drowning."},{"time":531800,"text":"Every morning, I asked myself\nhow much longer I could do it."},{"time":535520,"text":"I was allowed to bring my baby to work."},{"time":538720,"text":"I closed my office door\nwhile I rocked and shushed"},{"time":541880,"text":"and begged him to stop screaming\nso I wouldn't get in trouble."},{"time":545400,"text":"I hid behind that office door\nevery damn day"},{"time":547480,"text":"and cried while he screamed."},{"time":549440,"text":"I cried in the bathroom\nwhile I washed out the pump equipment."},{"time":553120,"text":"Every day, I cried all the way to work\nand all the way home again."},{"time":556280,"text":"I promised my boss that the work\nI didn't get done during the day,"},{"time":559440,"text":"I'd make up at night from home."},{"time":561120,"text":"I thought, there's just something\nwrong with me that I can't swing this.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":566520,"text":"So those are the mothers."},{"time":569160,"text":"What of the babies?"},{"time":570960,"text":"As a country, do we care\nabout the millions of babies"},{"time":573480,"text":"born every year to working mothers?"},{"time":575360,"text":"I say we don't,"},{"time":576720,"text":"not until they're of working\nand tax-paying and military-serving age."},{"time":580200,"text":"We tell them we'll see them in 18 years,"},{"time":582129,"text":"and getting there is kind of on them."},{"time":585854,"text":"One of the reasons I know this\nis that babies whose mothers"},{"time":588640,"text":"have 12 or more weeks at home with them"},{"time":590960,"text":"are more likely to get their vaccinations\nand their well checks in their first year,"},{"time":594960,"text":"so those babies are more protected\nfrom deadly and disabling diseases."},{"time":599680,"text":"But those things are hidden\nbehind images like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":606280,"text":"America has a message for new mothers\nwho work and for their babies."},{"time":611800,"text":"Whatever time you get together,\nyou should be grateful for it,"},{"time":615600,"text":"and you're an inconvenience"},{"time":618360,"text":"to the economy and to your employers."},{"time":621400,"text":"That narrative of gratitude\nruns through a lot of the stories I hear."}]},{"cues":[{"time":625960,"text":"A woman told me,"},{"time":627640,"text":"\"I went back at eight weeks\nafter my C-section"},{"time":629840,"text":"because my husband was out of work."},{"time":631680,"text":"Without me, my daughter\nhad failure to thrive."},{"time":634440,"text":"She wouldn't take a bottle."},{"time":635760,"text":"She started losing weight."},{"time":637400,"text":"Thankfully, my manager\nwas very understanding."},{"time":640240,"text":"He let my mom bring my baby,"},{"time":641800,"text":"who was on oxygen and a monitor,"},{"time":644120,"text":"four times a shift so I could nurse her.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":647960,"text":"There's a little club\nof countries in the world"},{"time":651360,"text":"that offer no national\npaid leave to new mothers."},{"time":655240,"text":"Care to guess who they are?"},{"time":657720,"text":"The first eight make up eight million\nin total population."},{"time":661680,"text":"They are Papua New Guinea,\nSuriname and the tiny island nations"},{"time":665200,"text":"of Micronesia, Marshall Islands,\nNauru, Niue, Palau and Tonga."},{"time":671440,"text":"Number nine is\nthe United States of America,"},{"time":673840,"text":"with 320 million people."},{"time":677320,"text":"Oh, that's it."},{"time":679680,"text":"That's the end of the list."},{"time":682280,"text":"Every other economy on the planet"},{"time":683920,"text":"has found a way to make some level\nof national paid leave work"},{"time":687840,"text":"for the people doing the work\nof the future of those countries,"},{"time":690840,"text":"but we say,\n\"We couldn't possibly do that.\""},{"time":694920,"text":"We say that the market\nwill solve this problem,"},{"time":697440,"text":"and then we cheer when corporations\noffer even more paid leave to the women"},{"time":701800,"text":"who are already the highest-educated\nand highest-paid among us."},{"time":705080,"text":"Remember that 88 percent?"},{"time":706920,"text":"Those middle- and low-income women\nare not going to participate in that."},{"time":711880,"text":"We know that there are staggering\neconomic, financial, physical"},{"time":717360,"text":"and emotional costs to this approach."},{"time":719920,"text":"We have decided --\ndecided, not an accident,"},{"time":723960,"text":"to pass these costs directly\non to working mothers and their babies."},{"time":727920,"text":"We know the price tag is higher\nfor low-income women,"},{"time":730600,"text":"therefore disproportionately\nfor women of color."},{"time":733400,"text":"We pass them on anyway."}]},{"cues":[{"time":735880,"text":"All of this is to America's shame."},{"time":738520,"text":"But it's also to America's risk."},{"time":742440,"text":"Because what would happen"},{"time":744360,"text":"if all of these individual\nso-called choices to have babies"},{"time":748440,"text":"started to turn into individual choices\nnot to have babies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":753320,"text":"One woman told me,"},{"time":755040,"text":"\"New motherhood is hard.\nIt shouldn't be traumatic."},{"time":758320,"text":"When we talk about expanding\nour family now,"},{"time":760600,"text":"we focus on how much time I would have\nto care for myself and a new baby."},{"time":764920,"text":"If we were to have to do it again\nthe same way as with our first,"},{"time":768240,"text":"we might stick with one kid.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":771800,"text":"The birthrate needed in America\nto keep the population stable"},{"time":774720,"text":"is 2.1 live births per woman."},{"time":776880,"text":"In America today, we are at 1.86."},{"time":780880,"text":"We need women to have babies,"},{"time":783200,"text":"and we are actively disincentivizing\nworking women from doing that."},{"time":787760,"text":"What would happen to work force,\nto innovation, to GDP,"},{"time":791000,"text":"if one by one, the working mothers\nof this country were to decide"},{"time":795160,"text":"that they can't bear\nto do this thing more than once?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":799680,"text":"I'm here today with only\none idea worth spreading,"},{"time":803200,"text":"and you've guessed what it is."},{"time":805360,"text":"It is long since time\nfor the most powerful country on Earth"},{"time":809080,"text":"to offer national paid leave"},{"time":811160,"text":"to the people doing the work\nof the future of this country"},{"time":813899,"text":"and to the babies\nwho represent that future."},{"time":816800,"text":"Childbirth is a public good."},{"time":818960,"text":"This leave should be state-subsidized."},{"time":821520,"text":"It should have no exceptions\nfor small businesses,"},{"time":824040,"text":"length of employment or entrepreneurs."},{"time":826520,"text":"It should be able\nto be shared between partners."},{"time":828920,"text":"I've talked today a lot about mothers,"},{"time":830920,"text":"but co-parents matter on so many levels."}]},{"cues":[{"time":835520,"text":"Not one more woman\nshould have to go back to work"},{"time":838640,"text":"while she is hobbling and bleeding."},{"time":841840,"text":"Not one more family should have\nto drain their savings account"},{"time":845520,"text":"to buy a few days\nof rest and recovery and bonding."},{"time":849200,"text":"Not one more fragile infant"},{"time":851520,"text":"should have to go directly\nfrom the incubator to day care"},{"time":854480,"text":"because his parents have used up\nall of their meager time"},{"time":857200,"text":"sitting in the NICU."},{"time":858840,"text":"Not one more working family\nshould be told that the collision"},{"time":861722,"text":"of their work, their needed work\nand their needed parenthood,"},{"time":866080,"text":"is their problem alone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":868760,"text":"The catch is that when this is happening\nto a new family, it is consuming,"},{"time":873440,"text":"and a family with a new baby\nis more financially vulnerable"},{"time":876240,"text":"than they've ever been before,"},{"time":877720,"text":"so that new mother cannot afford\nto speak up on her own behalf."},{"time":881680,"text":"But all of us have voices."},{"time":883920,"text":"I am done, done having babies,"},{"time":887520,"text":"and you might be pre-baby,"},{"time":889400,"text":"you might be post-baby,"},{"time":890800,"text":"you might be no baby."},{"time":892440,"text":"It should not matter."},{"time":894320,"text":"We have to stop framing this\nas a mother's issue,"},{"time":896760,"text":"or even a women's issue."},{"time":898480,"text":"This is an American issue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":902200,"text":"We need to stop buying the lie\nthat these images tell us."},{"time":905720,"text":"We need to stop being comforted by them."},{"time":908000,"text":"We need to question\nwhy we're told that this can't work"},{"time":910680,"text":"when we see it work\neverywhere all over the world."},{"time":914000,"text":"We need to recognize\nthat this American reality"},{"time":917800,"text":"is to our dishonor and to our peril."},{"time":921440,"text":"Because this is not,"},{"time":923640,"text":"this is not,"},{"time":925280,"text":"and this is not\nwhat a working mother looks like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":930200,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}